1
00:00:04,879 --> 00:00:07,109
(Episode 6)

2
00:00:12,950 --> 00:00:16,250
(Doctor Detective)

3
00:00:21,059 --> 00:00:22,159
Who is it?

4
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:25,730
Mr. Huh?

5
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:31,640
Don't you want to know...

6
00:00:32,570 --> 00:00:33,710
about the site in Namil?

7
00:00:39,439 --> 00:00:40,979
Your house is a mess.

8
00:00:40,979 --> 00:00:44,019
Cut to the chase.
Abut the site in Namil.

9
00:00:44,420 --> 00:00:45,680
Are you going to keep digging
into this case?

10
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:50,149
Why did you come that day?

11
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:51,690
Are you following me?

12
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:53,930
What a rude way of thanking me.

13
00:00:57,799 --> 00:00:59,759
This is the cellphone of the man
who tried to kill you.

14
00:01:00,199 --> 00:01:01,769
Why are you giving me this?

15
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:03,939
The man who tried to kill you...

16
00:01:05,570 --> 00:01:06,870
is trying to kill me too.

17
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:09,810
It's Executive Director Moh Sung Kuk
of TL Oshem.

18
00:01:10,679 --> 00:01:12,339
This is all his scheme.

19
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:14,509
From fabricating the site,
controlling the media,

20
00:01:14,510 --> 00:01:16,180
and even attempting to kill you.

21
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:20,550
I need to turn the tables
in order to live.

22
00:01:21,819 --> 00:01:22,889
That goes for you too.

23
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:25,460
Are you saying my life
depends on you?

24
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:27,929
UDC should reveal that the
dormitory was fabricated.

25
00:01:29,129 --> 00:01:31,729
I'll make the person involved
confess that he was responsible.

26
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,200
I'm checking the
surveillance cameras...

27
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,700
to find TL Oshem cars
going to the dormitory in Namil.

28
00:01:36,470 --> 00:01:37,770
I'll find something soon.

29
00:01:40,739 --> 00:01:41,939
How pitiful of TL.

30
00:01:42,140 --> 00:01:44,140
You're revealing the group's
critical secrets...

31
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:47,279
just to win
an internal power struggle?

32
00:01:47,679 --> 00:01:50,849
All I have to do is to announce
that it isn't the group's policy.

33
00:01:51,150 --> 00:01:53,020
That Oshem was solely responsible
for it.

34
00:01:55,849 --> 00:01:58,589
Choi Tae Young.
Is that what the chairman wants?

35
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,390
I know it isn't.

36
00:02:01,189 --> 00:02:02,629
This is your own doing.

37
00:02:03,129 --> 00:02:05,499
The chairman trusts
Executive Director Moh,

38
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,530
and you're just trying to
come between them.

39
00:02:10,569 --> 00:02:11,869
I'll pretend I didn't hear anything.

40
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:13,270
We'll continue
with the investigation.

41
00:02:16,039 --> 00:02:19,109
Don't even think about
using UDC.

42
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,480
Joong Eun, if you survived once,

43
00:02:23,050 --> 00:02:24,380
you should be thankful.

44
00:02:27,419 --> 00:02:29,349
I thought I'd died already
three years ago.

45
00:02:33,859 --> 00:02:35,889
Consider it as paying back a debt
and do as I say.

46
00:02:36,629 --> 00:02:37,699
And after that?

47
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:40,400
Open it to the media.
And bring down Mr. Moh.

48
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:43,329
You'll get the justice
that you want so much.

49
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,070
And I'll...

50
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:47,210
regain the chairman's trust.

51
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,069
And also,

52
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:54,010
leave UDC and live quietly.

53
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:57,550
Seo Rin should...

54
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:01,289
grow up with her mom.

55
00:03:07,289 --> 00:03:08,389
Are you...

56
00:03:09,229 --> 00:03:10,699
taking good care of Seo Rin?

57
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:12,930
Why?

58
00:03:14,129 --> 00:03:15,599
She called me earlier.

59
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:18,669
But we got disconnected right away.

60
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:21,169
She's doing well.

61
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:24,740
Since she's a kid,
of course, she'll miss her mom.

62
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,480
I'll take that as a yes and go now.
I'll be in touch.

63
00:03:37,189 --> 00:03:39,589
Take care of yourself. I beg of you.

64
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:44,160
Seo Rin needs you.

65
00:03:57,310 --> 00:04:00,240
(Doctor Detective)

66
00:04:06,449 --> 00:04:08,749
- Ms. Gong.
- You startled me.

67
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:13,389
(Chief Gong Il Sun)

68
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:17,160
So... In exchange for information,
he wants you to make an issue?

69
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:21,229
Choi Tae Young wants to take down
Moh Sung Kuk.

70
00:04:21,229 --> 00:04:23,669
We should thank him if
he wants to be a whistle-blower.

71
00:04:23,669 --> 00:04:25,269
He may be using us.

72
00:04:25,369 --> 00:04:28,009
Darn it. We've come too far anyway.

73
00:04:28,309 --> 00:04:30,369
The higher-ups refused
everything today.

74
00:04:33,010 --> 00:04:34,080
Let's do it.

75
00:04:35,710 --> 00:04:37,180
You can't go to the site anymore,
okay?

76
00:04:37,820 --> 00:04:38,820
Okay.

77
00:04:46,919 --> 00:04:48,489
How much did she drink?

78
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:50,730
Four bottles.

79
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,200
I guess it didn't go well with
her superiors.

80
00:04:56,229 --> 00:04:57,239
She stinks!

81
00:04:57,239 --> 00:05:00,399
She shouldn't have drunk
on an empty stomach.

82
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:02,110
It's not good for her stomach.

83
00:05:02,109 --> 00:05:05,879
We should get hangover soup
for lunch.

84
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:06,880
Should I have it delivered?

85
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:07,980
Let's eat out.

86
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:11,950
Ms. Doh is taking the morning off.

87
00:05:11,950 --> 00:05:13,150
Is she sick?

88
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:15,290
Have you heard from Mr. Huh?

89
00:05:15,289 --> 00:05:17,019
It's not normal for him
to come on time.

90
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:19,960
No. Something's going on.

91
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,030
A fling.

92
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:22,260
A what?

93
00:05:23,159 --> 00:05:24,699
A fling and not a fight?

94
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,430
Sure, it's a fling.

95
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:29,170
They left the office together,
yesterday.

96
00:05:29,169 --> 00:05:30,839
In Mr. Huh's car.

97
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:36,970
It feels like you're mine.
It feels like you're not...

98
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,480
Whatever. Let's just get coffee.

99
00:05:38,479 --> 00:05:40,979
(Namil Police Station)

100
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:42,210
(Medical Certificate)

101
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:43,680
It's Kim Do Hyeong's
medical certificate.

102
00:05:43,679 --> 00:05:46,479
He has diabetes
and needs insulin treatment.

103
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:48,889
I'd like to request
an official visit as a doctor.

104
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,260
Sir, could you come here a moment?

105
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,830
What is it?

106
00:06:03,869 --> 00:06:05,469
Visits aren't allowed to the UDC.

107
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:08,140
- Why not?
- You know why.

108
00:06:09,109 --> 00:06:11,709
That means other doctors
are allowed, right?

109
00:06:13,409 --> 00:06:16,709
Are you going to take responsibility
if he faints from low blood sugar?

110
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,720
Stop making a fuss!

111
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,990
I'll allow any other
qualified doctor.

112
00:06:23,989 --> 00:06:25,119
Now leave.

113
00:06:25,119 --> 00:06:26,759
We're busy, so please leave.

114
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:29,129
Get going, already!

115
00:06:29,630 --> 00:06:32,330
You have to leave clear proof...

116
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:34,730
that you left.

117
00:06:34,729 --> 00:06:37,469
We need a recording of you leaving
on the surveillance camera,

118
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:40,640
and I'll show up right then.

119
00:06:56,690 --> 00:06:57,990
Sir!

120
00:07:01,159 --> 00:07:03,089
I'm the other qualified doctor,

121
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:04,430
Huh Min Ki.

122
00:07:04,429 --> 00:07:07,059
This is my medical license.

123
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:10,370
Are you kidding me?

124
00:07:10,530 --> 00:07:13,000
You're both from UDC, aren't you?

125
00:07:12,999 --> 00:07:15,769
Yes. We're from UDC.

126
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:17,680
First, I'm not kidding.

127
00:07:17,679 --> 00:07:19,279
DKA.

128
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:21,850
There's a thing called
diabetic ketoacidosis.

129
00:07:21,849 --> 00:07:24,379
It's an acute complication that can
occur when a type 1 diabetic...

130
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:25,750
fails to regulate sugar levels.

131
00:07:25,749 --> 00:07:27,889
The patient could die
within 48 hours.

132
00:07:27,890 --> 00:07:30,490
Kim Do Hyeong is a type 1 diabetic.

133
00:07:30,489 --> 00:07:32,559
He's under
an emergency interrogation.

134
00:07:32,559 --> 00:07:35,559
We need some information
before we move him.

135
00:07:35,559 --> 00:07:37,759
- Come another time.
- I'm sure...

136
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:40,400
they're going to start lying
about some internal affairs.

137
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,500
Then...

138
00:07:43,299 --> 00:07:44,999
we have to bring up
the Human Rights Commission.

139
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,570
Is this Mr. Park of
the Human Rights Commission?

140
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:50,640
Yes, sir. Are you on your way?

141
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:54,150
Yes.
Reporter Byun is accompanying you?

142
00:07:54,510 --> 00:07:55,910
That's all right.

143
00:07:56,109 --> 00:07:59,349
These people are civil servants,
so they don't have portrait rights.

144
00:07:59,349 --> 00:08:01,749
I believe people have
the right to know.

145
00:08:01,849 --> 00:08:04,259
They should know that the police
are completely inconsiderate...

146
00:08:04,260 --> 00:08:05,560
- of human rights...
- All right, all right!

147
00:08:05,559 --> 00:08:07,759
Quit it with the act
and just leave the medicine.

148
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:11,130
Type 1 diabetics need
insulin injections, not medicine.

149
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:13,200
You need to be trained
to use the syringe.

150
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,670
Would you like to be trained?

151
00:08:14,669 --> 00:08:16,429
However, it will be
a violation of medical law.

152
00:08:16,429 --> 00:08:18,739
Do you even know what insulin is?

153
00:08:18,739 --> 00:08:20,469
Hey, doctor!

154
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:22,510
Go ahead.

155
00:08:23,909 --> 00:08:25,509
Yes, all right.

156
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:26,880
Good job.

157
00:08:27,349 --> 00:08:29,749
Make sure to reassure Do Hyeong
as soon as you get in.

158
00:08:29,749 --> 00:08:32,419
If he has mercury poisoning,
he could suffer from anxiety,

159
00:08:32,419 --> 00:08:35,189
paranoia, or show aggressiveness.

160
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,750
If he shows hypersensitivity,

161
00:08:36,749 --> 00:08:38,819
be sure to put me on the phone.

162
00:08:38,920 --> 00:08:40,730
You can tell them
I'm his usual doctor.

163
00:08:43,729 --> 00:08:44,899
Go away.

164
00:08:45,599 --> 00:08:47,299
Go away!

165
00:08:49,269 --> 00:08:50,999
I need to persuade the patient,

166
00:08:50,999 --> 00:08:52,499
so let him talk to his usual doctor.

167
00:08:52,499 --> 00:08:55,069
When he calms down,
drag it as long as you can.

168
00:08:57,170 --> 00:08:59,840
Remember that it's our only chance.

169
00:09:04,379 --> 00:09:05,449
It's all right.

170
00:09:10,349 --> 00:09:12,559
- Do Hyeong.
- Who is this?

171
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:15,690
It's me, Doh Joong Eun.
Calm down, Do Hyeong.

172
00:09:20,129 --> 00:09:21,469
Ms. Doh!

173
00:09:23,769 --> 00:09:25,199
I didn't do it.

174
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,040
I didn't do it, Ms. Doh.

175
00:09:29,170 --> 00:09:30,170
I know.

176
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,140
You didn't do anything wrong.

177
00:09:32,410 --> 00:09:35,650
You went to save Ha Rang,
but your hand shook.

178
00:09:35,649 --> 00:09:38,749
That's right, Ms. Doh.

179
00:09:39,119 --> 00:09:42,719
Now, don't talk and just listen.

180
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:45,960
It's because you're sick.
You were poisoned.

181
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,630
We're going to prove that.

182
00:09:49,090 --> 00:09:51,160
You can trust the doctor
in front of you.

183
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:56,870
Hang in there, just a bit.

184
00:09:57,229 --> 00:09:59,439
I brought long-acting insulin.

185
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,470
You've never tried this before,
so I'll teach you.

186
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:03,470
Okay.

187
00:10:06,779 --> 00:10:10,479
- Here. Hold this in your hand...
- Okay.

188
00:10:10,479 --> 00:10:12,279
and then...

189
00:10:12,649 --> 00:10:13,919
you hold your belly...

190
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,820
What are you doing? Don't touch him.

191
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:18,590
He needs to be trained
for the new prescription.

192
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:20,690
How am I supposed to treat him
without touching him?

193
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:22,430
Just finish it up and stand back.

194
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:25,860
You have to change the syringe...

195
00:10:25,859 --> 00:10:29,099
with every use.

196
00:10:29,099 --> 00:10:30,199
Okay.

197
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,540
For the dosage,

198
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:34,410
you can adjust it
with the dial on the end.

199
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:38,680
- I didn't do it.
- I know.

200
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:43,210
I'll do a final check-up.

201
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:44,950
Just a second...

202
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:50,820
Do Hyeong, push me back hard. Hurry!

203
00:10:52,389 --> 00:10:54,019
What are you doing?

204
00:10:54,090 --> 00:10:56,190
Hey! Stop that!

205
00:10:56,359 --> 00:10:58,599
- All right, kid!
- I didn't do it!

206
00:11:03,269 --> 00:11:07,039
Could you run a blood test
for the mercury, one last time?

207
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:09,540
It's Kim Do Hyeong's.

208
00:11:10,509 --> 00:11:11,539
What?

209
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:14,550
Mr. Huh! You're amazing!

210
00:11:14,910 --> 00:11:16,250
How did you do it?

211
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,950
It's a secret.

212
00:11:20,019 --> 00:11:22,489
Let's keep it a secret
until the results come out.

213
00:11:27,729 --> 00:11:30,529
- Good job.
- You, too.

214
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,960
Let's get Do Hyeong out of there.

215
00:11:42,970 --> 00:11:44,940
Ms. Gong. Ms. Gong!

216
00:11:45,379 --> 00:11:47,179
Look what I found.

217
00:11:47,649 --> 00:11:49,209
"Under the conditions
set by the president,"

218
00:11:49,210 --> 00:11:51,420
"the head of the
Undiagnosed Disease Center..."

219
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:53,080
"can open an evaluation committee
for the epidemiological survey..."

220
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,220
"on any substance or disease..."

221
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:58,090
"that is considered to be of harm
to the citizens."

222
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:00,290
The Epidemiological Survey
Evaluation Committee.

223
00:12:00,320 --> 00:12:02,190
It means there's a way.

224
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,930
- Do we have any kimchi?
- Why...

225
00:12:03,930 --> 00:12:06,430
would you mention kimchi now?

226
00:12:08,729 --> 00:12:10,869
I know you enjoy having cup noodles,

227
00:12:10,869 --> 00:12:14,239
so I bought some, just in case.

228
00:12:14,239 --> 00:12:16,139
What a smart guy!

229
00:12:18,479 --> 00:12:19,479
Ms. Byun,

230
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:22,810
don't you think I already brought up
the evaluation committee?

231
00:12:23,349 --> 00:12:24,849
The conditions...

232
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,950
set by the president...

233
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:29,250
needs consent from
the head of the corporation.

234
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:32,289
And the head says
he'll give permission...

235
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:34,430
only if we find proof
that it's poisoning.

236
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,860
It's just nonsense.

237
00:12:36,859 --> 00:12:38,329
How are we supposed to find it?

238
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:41,130
They got Kim Do Hyeong locked up
and won't even allow visits.

239
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:44,000
Joong Eun.

240
00:12:45,070 --> 00:12:46,300
Did you hear anything?

241
00:12:48,340 --> 00:12:50,210
Darn it, of course not.

242
00:12:50,269 --> 00:12:51,779
It hasn't even been a few days.

243
00:12:51,779 --> 00:12:54,409
Ms. Gong, ma'am. Cheer up!

244
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:58,980
I should cheer up, but darn it!

245
00:12:58,979 --> 00:13:01,489
Everyone's so afraid of TL!

246
00:13:01,489 --> 00:13:02,789
What if...

247
00:13:05,019 --> 00:13:06,419
we have the evidence?

248
00:13:07,660 --> 00:13:09,890
Come on!

249
00:13:09,989 --> 00:13:12,759
I'm sure Ms. Suk is almost done
with the analysis.

250
00:13:12,759 --> 00:13:13,759
What analysis?

251
00:13:15,599 --> 00:13:17,769
5, 4,

252
00:13:18,499 --> 00:13:19,539
3,

253
00:13:19,869 --> 00:13:21,839
2, 1!

254
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:25,110
Kim Do Hyeong's blood test results
are out!

255
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,750
The mercury is 60 times
the average level.

256
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,950
Do Hyeong didn't commit murder.

257
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:34,720
His hand was shaking
because of mercury poisoning.

258
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,850
But how did you collect his blood?

259
00:13:36,849 --> 00:13:38,859
We were able to visit him
using his medical condition...

260
00:13:38,859 --> 00:13:40,059
and collected his blood in secret.

261
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:42,430
I did it.

262
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:44,660
And you? This will be useless
if you got involved.

263
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:47,030
I've taken care of that.

